1. In order to create a cron job in centos7 run crontab -e
2. cron jobs will execute at a specific time and to set the time use the syntax below
3. the cron below will place the output of the ls command inside of a new file called text.txt

#m h dom mon dow command, Minute Hour DayOfMonth MonthNumber DayofWeek Command

44 14 * * * ls > /var/local/code/text.txt



the job below will update my centos7 os every month on the 23rd at 5:12AM


#m h dom mon dow command, Minute Hour DayOfMonth MonthNumber


12 5 23 * * sudo yum update



